"},"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/architecture":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/architecture","created":"20260305110616403","modified":"20260305110616403","rdt.order":"2","rdt.plugin-key":"git-int","rdt.plugin-name":"git integration","rdt.plugin-subtitle":"Git version control for individual tiddlers from the editor","rdt.section":"Architecture","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Three-layer architecture

* ''Browser UI'' — `panel.tid` (3 tabs), `toolbar-button.tid`, `styles.tid`
* ''Action widget'' — `<$action-git>` XHR bridge between UI and server
* ''Server routes'' — `route.js` (GET), `route-post.js` (POST), `git-utils.js` (shared)

!! Components

|!Component |!Layer |!Role |
|`route.js` |Server |GET ops: log, show, stash-list, stash-show, stash-drop |
|`route-post.js` |Server |POST ops: diff, snapshot, stash-push |
|`git-utils.js` |Server |Shared: `resolveTiddlerPath`, `parseTidFields`, `parseTidBody`, `execGit`, `sendJson` |
|`action-git.js` |Browser |`<$action-git>` widget — XHR bridge, writes to `$:/temp/` |
|`panel.tid` |Browser |EditTemplate UI — 3 tabs (Diff/Commit/Stash) |
|`toolbar-button.tid` |Browser |Editor toolbar button |

!! Why POST for diff/snapshot/stash-push

The server's `$tw.wiki` may not have the latest browser edits due to syncer polling delay. POST allows the browser to send current draft field values.

!! Diff model

All fields compared uniformly. Server returns `fieldChanges` array with per-field diffs.

!! State tiddlers

* `$:/state/rimir/git-int/<title>` — panel open/closed
* `$:/state/rimir/git-int/tab/<title>` — active tab
* `$:/temp/rimir/git-int/<title>/<op>` — operation response data

!! Security

* No arbitrary paths — validates against `$tw.boot.files`
* Input validation — hash `/^[a-f0-9]{4,40}$/`, index `/^\d+$/`
* `execFile` with array args — no shell injection
* CSRF header required (`X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki`)

!! Key data flows

* ''Diff'': draft fields → POST → `git show` → compare all fields → `fieldChanges`
* ''Per-field revert'': click undo → delete/set field on draft → re-run diff
* ''Commit'': message → POST snapshot → write `.tid` → `git add` + `git commit` → auto-refresh log
* ''Restore'': click restore → GET show → replace all draft fields (remove absent ones)

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">Field order is preserved when writing `.tid` files to avoid creating false diffs in git.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
"},"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/dev-workflow":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/dev-workflow","created":"20260305110616404","modified":"20260305110616404","rdt.order":"3","rdt.plugin-key":"git-int","rdt.plugin-name":"git integration","rdt.plugin-subtitle":"Git version control for individual tiddlers from the editor","rdt.section":"Dev Workflow","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Plugin files

|!File |!Role |
|`plugin.info` |Plugin metadata |
|`git-utils.js` |Shared library (module-type: library) |
|`route.js` |GET route (module-type: route) |
|`route-post.js` |POST route (module-type: route) |
|`action-git.js` |Action widget (module-type: widget) |
|`toolbar-button.tid` |Editor toolbar button (tagged) |
|`panel.tid` |Edit template panel (tagged) |
|`icon.tid` |Toolbar icon (tagged) |
|`styles.tid` |CSS stylesheet |

!! Restart rules

All changes require server restart (JS modules + plugin shadow tiddlers).

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="tip">
<$fill $name="body">After restarting, do a hard refresh (Ctrl+F5) in the browser to clear cached JS.</$fill>
</$transclude>

!! Design decisions

* POST for draft fields — server wiki may lag behind browser due to syncer polling
* Dedicated routes (not runner plugin) — needs response data handling
* Two route files — clean separation by HTTP method
* Uniform field handling — text field not treated specially
* Full field restore — replaces all fields, removes absent ones
* Context-preserving revert — echoes hash/index back to browser
* Auto-load on panel open — runs `op="diff"` when panel opens

!! API reference

|!Method |!Endpoint |!Operations |
|GET |`/api/git` |log, show, stash-list, stash-show, stash-drop |
|POST |`/api/git` |diff, snapshot, stash-push |

All responses include `op` and `status` fields.

!! Debugging

* Server logs: `$tw.utils.Logger("git-int")`
* Browser: check `$:/temp/rimir/git-int/<title>/<op>` tiddlers
* Network: DevTools Network tab for request/response inspection

</$fill>
</$transclude>
"},"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/examples":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/examples","created":"20260305110616404","modified":"20260305110616404","rdt.order":"4","rdt.plugin-key":"git-int","rdt.plugin-name":"git integration","rdt.plugin-subtitle":"Git version control for individual tiddlers from the editor","rdt.section":"Examples","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Full diff workflow

# Open a tiddler for editing
# Click the git icon in the editor toolbar to open the panel
# The Diff tab loads automatically, showing field-by-field changes vs HEAD
# Changed fields show old and new values; added fields show only new; removed fields show only old
# Click the undo icon on any field to revert just that field

!! Commit with message

# Make edits to a tiddler and open the git panel
# Switch to the Commit tab
# Enter a commit message in the text field
# Click "Commit" — the plugin writes draft fields to disk, runs `git add` + `git commit`
# The log below refreshes automatically to show the new commit

!! View commit history

# Open the git panel on any tiddler
# Switch to the Commit tab — the log shows recent commits (up to 20)
# Click "Show" on any entry to view the tiddler's state at that commit
# Click "Diff" to compare the current draft against that specific commit
# Click "Restore" to replace all draft fields with that commit's version

!! Stash and restore

# Open the git panel and switch to the Stash tab
# Enter an optional message and click "Stash" — saves current draft to git stash
# The stash list below shows all stashed versions
# Click "Show" to preview, "Diff" to compare, or "Restore" to apply
# Click "Drop" to remove a stash entry

!! Per-field revert

When viewing a diff, each changed field has an undo button. Clicking it:

* For ''changed'' fields: resets the draft field to the old value
* For ''added'' fields: removes the field from the draft
* For ''removed'' fields: restores the field to the draft

After reverting, the diff re-runs to reflect the updated state.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
"},"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/faq":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/faq","created":"20260305110616404","modified":"20260305110616404","rdt.order":"5","rdt.plugin-key":"git-int","rdt.plugin-name":"git integration","rdt.plugin-subtitle":"Git version control for individual tiddlers from the editor","rdt.section":"FAQ","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Q: Why does diff use POST instead of GET?

The browser may have unsaved draft edits that haven't reached the server yet (syncer polling delay). POST lets the browser send current draft field values so the diff is always accurate against what you're actually editing.

!! Q: What if nothing has been committed yet?

The diff operation will return an error because `git show HEAD:<path>` fails when there's no commit history for that file. Commit at least once before using diff.

!! Q: Can I undo a commit?

Not from the plugin UI. Use `git revert` or `git reset` from the command line. The plugin is intentionally limited to forward-only operations (commit, stash, restore) to avoid destructive actions from the browser.

!! Q: Why per-tiddler operations instead of bulk?

Each tiddler is a separate `.tid` file in the git repo. Per-tiddler operations map cleanly to git's file-level semantics and keep the UI focused on the tiddler you're currently editing.

!! Q: What about binary tiddlers?

Binary files (images, PDFs) don't have `.tid` format with field headers. The plugin resolves paths via `$tw.boot.files` which tracks all tiddler-to-file mappings, but diffing only works meaningfully for text-based `.tid` files.

!! Q: Why two separate route files?

Clean separation by HTTP method. `route.js` handles GET (read-only: log, show, stash-list, stash-show, stash-drop) and `route-post.js` handles POST (draft-aware: diff, snapshot, stash-push). This makes the security model clear — POST routes receive and write data, GET routes only read.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
"},"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/overview":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/overview","created":"20260305110616404","modified":"20260305110616404","rdt.hub-category":"editor-vcs","rdt.hub-category-name":"Editor & Version Control","rdt.hub-order":"2","rdt.order":"1","rdt.plugin-key":"git-int","rdt.plugin-name":"git integration","rdt.plugin-subtitle":"Git version control for individual tiddlers from the editor","rdt.section":"Overview","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Version control individual tiddlers directly from the TiddlyWiki editor. Click the git icon in the editor toolbar to open a panel with three tabs: Diff, Commit, and Stash.

!! Features

* ''Diff tab'' — shows changes vs git reference, per-field inline diffs, revert buttons per field, auto-loads on panel open
* ''Commit tab'' — optional message (default "Snapshot: <title>"), history with diff/restore buttons
* ''Stash tab'' — save/apply/drop stash entries, compare stash to draft
* ''Draft-aware'' — browser sends current draft fields to server (server's `$tw.wiki` may lag behind)
* ''Uniform field handling'' — all fields compared equally (text is not special)
* ''Non-destructive'' — diff/restore/revert only modify browser draft, never git directly
* ''Per-tiddler state'' — each tiddler has independent git panel state

!! Prerequisites

* Git repository with tiddler files tracked
* TiddlyWiki running in Node.js server mode

!! Quick start

# Ensure your wiki directory is a git repo with tiddler files committed
# Open any tiddler for editing
# Click the git icon in the editor toolbar
# The Diff tab auto-loads showing changes since last commit

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="warning">
<$fill $name="body">Commit, stash, and drop operations modify git history permanently. Diff, restore, apply, and revert only modify the browser draft.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
"},"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/reference":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/git-int/doc/reference","created":"20260305110616405","modified":"20260305110616405","rdt.order":"6","rdt.plugin-key":"git-int","rdt.plugin-name":"git integration","rdt.plugin-subtitle":"Git version control for individual tiddlers from the editor","rdt.section":"Reference","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! GET /api/git

|!Parameter |!Used by |!Format |!Description |
|`op` |all |`log` `show` `stash-list` `stash-show` `stash-drop` |Operation name |
|`title` |all except stash-list |tiddler title |Target tiddler |
|`count` |log |integer (default 20) |Max log entries |
|`hash` |show |`/^[a-f0-9]{4,40}$/` |Commit hash |
|`index` |stash-show, stash-drop |`/^\d+$/` |Stash index |

!! POST /api/git

Request body (JSON):

|!Field |!Used by |!Description |
|`op` |all |`diff` `snapshot` `stash-push` |
|`title` |all |Original tiddler title |
|`fields` |all |Current draft fields object |
|`message` |snapshot, stash-push |Commit/stash message |
|`hash` |diff |Compare against specific commit |
|`index` |diff |Compare against stash entry |

CSRF header required: `X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki`

!! Response JSON

All responses include `op` and `status` (`"ok"` or `"error"`).

|!Op |!Extra fields |
|log |`entries: [{hash, date, message}]` |
|show, stash-show |`content` (body text), `fields` (parsed header) |
|diff |`fieldChanges: [{field, type, oldVal, newVal}]`, `hasDiff`, `diffLabel`, `hash`, `index` |
|snapshot |`output` (git commit output) |
|stash-list |`entries: [{index, ref, date, message}]` |
|stash-push |`output` (git stash output) |
|stash-drop |`output` (git stash drop output) |

!! <$action-git> widget

|!Attribute |!Description |
|`op` |Operation: log, show, diff, snapshot, stash-list, stash-show, stash-drop, stash-push |
|`title` |Original (non-draft) tiddler title |
|`hash` |Git commit hash (show, diff) |
|`message` |Commit/stash message (snapshot, stash-push) |
|`draft` |Draft tiddler title (diff, snapshot, stash-push, show, stash-show) |
|`index` |Stash index number (stash-show, stash-drop, diff) |

!! State tiddlers

|!Pattern |!Purpose |
|`$:/state/rimir/git-int/<title>` |Panel open/closed |
|`$:/state/rimir/git-int/tab/<title>` |Active tab name |
|`$:/temp/rimir/git-int/<title>/<op>` |Operation response (JSON) |
|`$:/temp/rimir/git-int/_global/stash-list` |Global stash list response |
