<$fill $name="body">

!! $tw.boot.files path resolution

`$tw.boot.files[title]` maps tiddler titles to filesystem paths. The `resolveTiddlerPath` utility in `git-utils.js` uses this to find the `.tid` file for any tiddler. Returns `null` if the tiddler has no filesystem backing (e.g., shadow tiddlers).

!! execFile vs exec

The plugin uses `child_process.execFile("git", args)` with an array of arguments instead of `child_process.exec("git " + args)`. This avoids shell injection — arguments are passed directly to the git process without shell interpretation.

!! Route module-type

Both `route.js` and `route-post.js` use `module-type: route`. They export `method` (`"GET"` or `"POST"`), `path` (regex), and `handler`. POST routes also export `bodyFormat: "string"` to tell TW to read the request body as a string (parsed as JSON in the handler).

!! Action widget XHR pattern

`action-git.js` uses `XMLHttpRequest` directly (not `tm-http-request`) because it needs response data handling. The widget:

# Sets `$:/temp/rimir/git-int/<title>/<op>` to `{status: "loading"}`
# Sends GET or POST request with CSRF header
# On response: parses JSON, writes result to the temp tiddler
# For restore ops: reads response fields and writes them onto the draft tiddler

!! EditTemplate tags

`panel.tid` is tagged `$:/tags/EditTemplate` with `list-after: $:/core/ui/EditTemplate/controls`. This places the git panel inside every tiddler's edit view, below the toolbar controls. The panel is hidden by default — only visible when the state tiddler is set to `"open"`.

!! $:/temp/ tiddlers

Tiddlers with `$:/temp/` prefix are:

* Not saved to disk by the filesystem adaptor
* Not included in the skinny tiddler list (excluded by default filter)
* Not persisted across page reloads
* Ideal for transient UI state like operation responses

</$fill>
</$transclude>
